# BYOS Design Philosophy

## Mission

BYOS is for forking. Authors write recipes in **React + Tailwind** with minimal BYOS-specific API. Verify locally at `/recipes/[slug]` (React, PNG, BMP) before deploy (`docs/recipes.md`). Framework HTML, Puppeteer, and heavy runtime are parity/legacy lanes only.

## Authoring

- Recipes: Zod schemas + `RecipeDefinition` in `app/(app)/recipes/screens/<slug>/`.
- Layout via **`ScreenProfile`** (`bitDepth`, `colors`, `isCompact`) ‚Äî not `screen--*` Framework classes (`docs/trmnl-screen-design.md`).
- Wrap Takumi-safe UI in **`PreSatori`**; reuse `components/trmnl/` primitives.
- `REACT_RENDERER=browser` and Liquid/Puppeteer are optional ‚Äî not the default (`lib/recipes/render/rasterize.ts`).

## Pipeline

Default: React ‚Üí PreSatori ‚Üí Takumi/Satori ‚Üí sharp quantizer ‚Üí BMP/WebP. Do not add browser-head deps to the default path. Do not port Framework Runtime (clamp, overflow, fit-value, `md:2bit:` prefixes) into Takumi.

## Multi-device (PR #78 / #80)

No longer OG 2-bit-only ‚Äî support color e-ink, larger canvases, 4/8/16-bit grayscale. **`data/trmnl/palettes.json`** is the single source of truth. Derive dither `levels` from `getPaletteGrayLevels(palette)`; use `screen.bitDepth` / `screen.colors` in React ‚Äî never an independent grayscale knob.

## Quantization

Avoid legacy offline optimizations that create stair-step text artifacts ‚Äî worse than honest quantization. Hard-quantize to the target palette: 2-bit ‚Üí 2 levels, higher bit-depth ‚Üí discrete levels, color ‚Üí Lab nearest-color (`lib/render/device-image.ts`).

```typescript
// BAD: const levels = params.grayscale ?? 2;
// GOOD:
const levels = getPaletteGrayLevels(palette);
```

## Graphics

Three content policies:

1. **Text / icons / SVG** ‚Äî hard snap on full frame; stay crisp.
2. **UI fills** ‚Äî Tailwind `dither-*` on 1-bit; solid color on color e-ink.
3. **Photos** ‚Äî author chooses method via `renderSettings.imageDither` or
   `prepareForDevice` / `<DeviceImage>`; default **Bayer** (retro, local, fast).
   Also: `white-noise`, `floyd-steinberg` (opt-in smooth gradients). Gray reduction
   uses perceptual **Lab L\*** (`lib/render/luminance.ts`), not BT.601 average.

- Tailwind grays (`dither-50` via `utils/dither-patterns.ts`): pipeline quantizes to device dither ‚Äî no prep needed.
- Photos/complex images: `prepareDeviceImage` + `prepareForDevice`; CPU-friendly methods, not opaque runtime magic.
- Color e-ink: dither to palette colors (`docs/trmnl/eink-palette-mapping.md`).

## Agent checklist

Forker-friendly React/Tailwind? `palettes.json` + `ScreenProfile`? Hard quantize, not text smoothing? Takumi default? Verifiable at `/recipes/[slug]`?
